To determine any variation in the incidence of influenza A(H1N1)pdm09 according to the age of the patient from whom the sample was obtained, the subject group was stratified into the following age groups: 0–19 (n = 68), 20–39 (n = 105), 40–59 (n = 162), 60–79 (n = 243), and ≥80 years (n = 171) (Table 1
). We compared the distributions of POS vs. NEG results from Table 1 (n = 738) across the age groups using a chi-square test. The chi-square statistic was 41.9976 (p <
 0.00001), which confirmed a significant variation in the incidence of A(H1N1)pdm09 by age.
